Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Rose Garden about the American Rescue Plan, emphasizing that help has arrived for workers, students, families, and small businesses. She thanked Speaker Nancy Pelosi, Majority Leader Chuck Schumer, and all members of Congress who supported the legislation. Harris praised President Joe Biden for his empathy and dedication to helping the American people. She highlighted the concrete and tangible benefits of the plan, such as direct relief payments and child tax credits. Harris concluded by expressing gratitude to Biden for his leadership and the impact the bill will have for generations to come.